      <memberdef kind="define" id="group__group__funcmacro__byteorder_1ga9d00fa152fe6e580048035a6f8d9379c" prot="public" static="no">
        <name>wxFORCE_LINK_THIS_MODULE</name>
        <param><defname>moduleName</defname></param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This macro can be used in conjunction with the <ref refid="group__group__funcmacro__byteorder_1ga063c051259bc80da29444f51cfdbfaaa" kindref="member">wxFORCE_LINK_MODULE()</ref> macro to force the linker to include in its output a specific object file. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>In particular, you should use this macro in the source file which you want to force for inclusion. The <computeroutput>moduleName</computeroutput> needs to be a name not already in use in other <ref refid="group__group__funcmacro__byteorder_1ga9d00fa152fe6e580048035a6f8d9379c" kindref="member">wxFORCE_LINK_THIS_MODULE()</ref> macros, but is not required to be e.g. the same name of the source file (even if it&apos;s a good choice).</para><para>Include <ulink url="file:">file:</ulink> <verbatim>#include &lt;wx/link.h&gt; </verbatim> </para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
