    <briefdescription>
<para>The endian-ness issues (that is the difference between big-endian and little-endian architectures) are important for the portable programs working with the external binary data (for example, data files or data coming from network) which is usually in some fixed, platform-independent format. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The macros are helpful for transforming the data to the correct format. </para>    </detaileddescription>
